	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65028625">I was once the director of a university lab and one obvious way to publish more is to take a paper that got accepted in one journal and "re-work it" to publish it again.  You have to make the second paper seem like an advance over the first and the easiest way to do that is to simply add unnecessary content.  If it is longer and has a new graph or image, you are good to go. Each succeeding paper tends to be less clear than the previous.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65028625">

